   631	- **Branch-protection update** to require the new
   632	  `python-test-postgres` job — defer to a follow-up after a few
   633	  clean runs (same posture 10a took for `compose-smoke`).
   634	
   635	## Risks / things to watch
   636	
   637	- **`uv sync --frozen` in Docker requires `uv.lock`.** If the lock
   638	  file ever becomes stale relative to `pyproject.toml`, `--frozen`
   639	  fails the build. We commit `uv.lock`; the existing `python-lint`
   640	  / `python-typecheck` / `python-test` jobs all use `--frozen`
   641	  successfully, so this is consistent with current discipline.
   642	
   643	- **`postgres:16.6-alpine` image hash.** 10a pinned the major.minor;
   644	  we should consider pinning the digest in CI for absolute
   645	  determinism. Currently we don't — out of scope for this chunk.
   646	
   647	- **Compose `configs:` vs bind-mounting the experiment-config
   648	  YAML.** Compose configs are nicer (immutable, declared centrally)
   649	  but only work in Swarm or a recent-enough Compose v2. The
   650	  fallback is a `volumes:` entry mounting the file. Verify whether
   651	  CI's Compose version supports `configs:` in non-Swarm mode; if
   652	  not, fall back to a regular bind-mount. (Compose v2.20+ supports
   653	  it; CI's `ubuntu-latest` ships v2.27+; should be fine.)
   654	
   655	- **psycopg's binary wheel availability on Linux/arm64.** Most
   656	  platforms have wheels for `psycopg[binary]>=3.2`; if a CI runner
   657	  doesn't, fall back to building from source — adds ~30s to image
   658	  build. Acceptable.
   659	
   660	- **Image bloat.** The shared image will be ~400MB (Python slim +
   661	  workspace + git). If this becomes problematic later, multi-stage
   662	  with a `wheels` builder is the standard fix; not needed yet.
   663	
   664	- **The web-ui's `--repo-path` flag.** The web-ui needs the bare
   665	  repo for the work-refs admin sub-page. We mount it. The flag
   666	  also gates the entire implementer module (chunk 9c), which the
   667	  scripted implementer-host service makes redundant — both modules
   668	  now race for the same tasks. **In Compose**, only the
   669	  implementer-host should claim implement tasks; the web-ui's
   670	  implementer module is for human override / debugging. We keep
   671	  both available; the user opens whichever they prefer. Document
   672	  this in the compose README.

